>  Would it make sense to create a separate pull request for master or can we simply execute generate.groovy later when this is merged from tp32 into master?

I think it's fine to do it on merge to master. Generally speaking, I think a separate PR is only useful when there is potential for big conflicts and the PR is helpful for separate evaluation of the merge work. As long as you get both master and tp32 set and working locally before you push, you can generally get by without the second PR. The worst is when you push tp32 but then don't have master working right and there is a delay getting master up to date as it then has the potential to slow down other folks working on the repo.

